        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3254070179" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer215103411958918831">A feel-good story which crams together an endearing/annoying teenager, a father figure, emotionally unavailable parents, hookers, a road trip, a death scene, religion, pearls of wisdom, an interracial friendship, and some humor, all in 85 pages (the French edition). It felt like the French answer to Coelho. A decent &quot;roman de gare&quot; (though it can hardly be called a novel), but no more than that.</span>
  <span id="freeText215103411958918831" style="display:none">A feel-good story which crams together an endearing/annoying teenager, a father figure, emotionally unavailable parents, hookers, a road trip, a death scene, religion, pearls of wisdom, an interracial friendship, and some humor, all in 85 pages (the French edition). It felt like the French answer to Coelho. A decent "roman de gare" (though it can hardly be called a novel), but no more than that.</span>
