        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3327309796?book_show_action=true">May 09, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Vera" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Vera" href="/user/show/26398034-vera">Vera</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9783250600558" href="/book/show/120462.Monsieur_Ibrahim_und_die_Blumen_des_Koran">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26398034-vera?shelf=books-i-own">books-i-own</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer3327309796&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3327309796" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12115918205198128782">This little story takes place in Paris of the 1960s. The protagonist is a 11 year old Jewish boy, Moses, living with his father, who doesn‘t seem to love him and always talks about his older brother Popol, who actually left together with Moses mother when Moses was still a baby. Moses searches for love and recognition by visiting prostitutes, and somehow is intrigued by Monsieur Ibrahim, an ‚Arab‘ (it turns out he is actually a Turkish Muslim) running a little store in Moses’ street. Monsieur Ib</span>
  <span id="freeText12115918205198128782" style="display:none">This little story takes place in Paris of the 1960s. The protagonist is a 11 year old Jewish boy, Moses, living with his father, who doesn‘t seem to love him and always talks about his older brother Popol, who actually left together with Moses mother when Moses was still a baby. Moses searches for love and recognition by visiting prostitutes, and somehow is intrigued by Monsieur Ibrahim, an ‚Arab‘ (it turns out he is actually a Turkish Muslim) running a little store in Moses’ street. Monsieur Ibrahim teaches Moses some very useful lessons. When Moses‘ father leaves and later takes his own life, Monsieur Ibrahim even adopts Moses. <br /><br />I loved the unexpected sides in the story – That Moses wouldn‘t acknowledge his mother as his mother, or Monsieur Ibrahim’s accident, just when everything seems to develop so happily for the boy. But life is not fair nor is it a fairy tale, and so neither is this story.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12115918205198128782" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


