<div id="review_1708565286" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1708565286" />
    <a title="Tourya" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/19893207-tourya"><img alt="Tourya" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1420016942p2/19893207.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1708565286?book_show_action=true">Jul 25, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tourya" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tourya" href="/user/show/19893207-tourya">Tourya</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1708565286" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13819902899455544510">If you liked &quot;The elegance of the hedgehog &quot; from Muriel Barbery or &quot;la vie devant sois&quot; (sorry don&apos;t have the title in English) from Romain Gary you will enjoy this one. The themes are very similar so for me this read was not incredible... It felt as if the author used some subjects to make the story appealing : hookers, religion, soufism, parents, road trip, ... But it&apos;s a quick read so still recommending it.</span>
  <span id="freeText13819902899455544510" style="display:none">If you liked "The elegance of the hedgehog " from Muriel Barbery or "la vie devant sois" (sorry don't have the title in English) from Romain Gary you will enjoy this one. The themes are very similar so for me this read was not incredible... It felt as if the author used some subjects to make the story appealing : hookers, religion, soufism, parents, road trip, ... But it's a quick read so still recommending it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13819902899455544510" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


